{"title_page": "Emmanuel \"Mannie\" Essien", "text_new": "{{short description|Nigerian Musician}}\n\n{{Use British English|date=April 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2015}}\n{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] -->\n|birth_name        = Emmanuel Essien\n| image       =\n| caption     =\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1977|03|26|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Jos, Plateau State]], (Nigeria)\n| death_date  =\n| death_place =\n| occupation  = On Air Personality, Musician, Voice over artist, singer, Compere, and former actor\n| nationality = Nigerian\n| genre       =\n| subject     =\n| influences  =\n| influenced  =\n| period      = 2004\u2013Present\n| awards      =\n| Twitter     = @themanmannie\n}}\n\n'''Emmanuel Essien'''also known as '''Alien Em'' was (born March 26th 1977) is a [[Nigerian]] [[Musician]], known as a [[radio presenter]] on 96.9 Coolfm <ref>{{cite web|url=https://coolfm.ng/oap/emmanuel-essien:/ \n\n\n==Personal life==\n\nEssien is married to Grace Edewede Essien with whom he has two children Michael and Eleanor. \n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Essien, Emmanuel}}\n[[Category:1977 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Nigerian radio personalities]]\n[[Category:Nigerian television personalities]]\n[[Category:Nigerian male voice actors]]\n[[Category:University of Calabar alumni]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Plateau State]]\n[[Category:21st-century Nigerian male actors]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Nigerian actor}}\n{{Multiple issues|{{BLP sources|date=April 2015}}{{Notability|Biographies|date=May 2015}}{{Orphan|date=May 2015}}}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2015}}\n{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] -->\n|birth_name        = Emmanuel Essien\n| image       =\n| caption     =\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1977|03|26|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Jos, Plateau State]], (Nigeria)\n| death_date  =\n| death_place =\n| occupation  = Air Personality, Voice over artist, singer, Compere, and former actor\n| nationality = Nigerian\n| genre       =\n| subject     =\n| influences  =\n| influenced  =\n| period      = 2004\u2013Present\n| awards      =\n| Twitter     =\n}}\n\n'''Emmanuel Essien''' (born 26 March 1977) is a [[Nigeria]]n [[radio presenter]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.punchng.com/spice/celebrity-couple/my-wife-knows-women-ive-dated-mannie/ |title=My wife knows women I've dated - Mannie |publisher=Punchmg.com |accessdate=2015-05-18 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150427211850/http://www.punchng.com/spice/celebrity-couple/my-wife-knows-women-ive-dated-mannie/ |archivedate=27 April 2015 |df=dmy }}</ref> [[voice over]] artist, singer, compere, and former actor.\nHe was the host of the ''Good Morning Nigeria'' show on Nigerian radio station, 96.9 Cool FM, in [[Lagos]]. In March 2015, he was nominated for Hollywood's Nickelodeon Kids Choice Award in USA for best Nigerian On Air Personality.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://thenet.ng/2011/12/photos-from-fab-night-out-nominees-unveiling/emmanuel-mannie-essien-nominee-on-air-personality-of-the-year-copy/|title=Emmanuel Mannie Essien - Nominee, On Air personality of the Year  - Nigerian Entertainment Today - Nigeria's Top Website for News, Gossip, Comedy, Videos, Blogs, Events, Weddings, Nollywood, Celebs, Scoop and Games|work=Nigerian Entertainment Today - Nigeria's Top Website for News, Gossip, Comedy, Videos, Blogs, Events, Weddings, Nollywood, Celebs, Scoop and Games|access-date=2017-03-08|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\n==Life and work==\n\n===Early life and education===\nEssien was born in [[Jos Plateau]] in Northern Nigeria to retired principal Obong Jo. The last of six children, Mannie grew up in many parts of Nigeria, including Gombe and Bauchi state. He was in Gombe state from 1978 to 1987 where his father was the first provost of NTTC Gombe, an institution of higher learning. Then in [[Calabar]] he completed his primary education at Auntie Margaret International school in 1989, after which he attended Federal Government College Enugu in 1992 then later finishing at [[Federal Government College Ikot Ekpene]] in 1996. He gained admission to study linguistics at the [[University of Calabar]] in 1999, graduating in 2003.\n\n==Career==\nEssien wrote songs as a young boy, and tried out in talent competitions like the Golden Tones with Benson and Hedges and the first Project Fame in 2004 representing Nigeria in South Africa. Broadcaster Olisa Adibua, at Cool FM later spoke to the manager about giving him a job as a producer.  Essien went on to produce [[radio sweeper]]s and [[Station identification|station IDs]] for Cool FM, Wazobia FM, and Nigeria Info Fm.\nHis manager, engineer Amin Moussalli, advised him to go into radio presenting.\n\n===Television and radio===\nEssien is the host of the TV cooking competition, ''[[Knorr Taste Quest]]'', and is a co-host on '''Discovery 234'' on [[DStv]].\n\nOn radio he hosts the ''Good Morning Nigeria Show'', and is a voiceover and audio jingle producer for brands including MTN, Coca-Cola, Chicken Republic, and FCMB.\n\n===Music===\nEssien signed to Rayramon Records Australia, and released his debut single in 2015 called ''Moving On'' featuring musician Ray Ramon and DJ Andromeda from the U.K. The music was co-written by Jenny Ramon from Australia.  \"Moving On\" has received airplay on radio stations{{Which|date=April 2015}} in Nigeria, Australia, and the UK.\n\n===Awards===\n\nIn 2014, his show \"Good Morning Nigeria Show\" was awarded the most outstanding radio show in the Nigerian Broadcasters Merit Awards.\nHe also won favourite On Air Personality at Hollywood's Nickelodeon Kids Choice awards in Hollywood USA in March, 2015.\n\n==Personal life==\n\nEssien is married to Grace Edewede Essien with whom he has two children Michael and Eleanor. He lives in Mbiabong in [[Uyo]], [[Akwa Ibom State]], Nigeria.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Essien, Emmanuel Mannie}}\n[[Category:1977 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Nigerian radio personalities]]\n[[Category:Nigerian television personalities]]\n[[Category:Nigerian male voice actors]]\n[[Category:University of Calabar alumni]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Plateau State]]\n[[Category:21st-century Nigerian male actors]]\n", "name_user": "Mannie77", "label": "vandal", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emmanuel_%22Mannie%22_Essien"}
